That’s a useful next step—adding a condition so reminders stop once you’ve logged the reply date or changed the status. You can adapt the same little script like this:

```javascript
function checkSubmissions() {
  var sheet = SpreadsheetApp.getActiveSpreadsheet().getSheetByName("Submissions");
  var data = sheet.getDataRange().getValues();
  var today = new Date();
  var alertList = [];
  for (var i = 1; i < data.length; i++) {
    var sentDate = new Date(data[i][0]);      // Column A = Date Sent
    var responseDate = data[i][5];            // Column F = Response Date
    var status = data[i][4];                  // Column E = Status
    var diff = (today - sentDate) / (1000*60*60*24);

    // trigger only if over 90 days, still marked In Review, and no response date
    if (diff > 90 && status === "In Review" && responseDate === "") {
      alertList.push(data[i][1]);  // Column B = Venue / Contest
    }
  }
  if (alertList.length > 0) {
    MailApp.sendEmail({
      to: "YOUR_EMAIL@domain.com",
      subject: "Submission Reminder – Small Signal",
      body: "These entries have passed 90 days with no response: " + alertList.join(", ")
    });
  }
}
```

Set your daily or weekly trigger the same way as before.  
Now, when you either type a *Response Date* or change the *Status* to something other than “In Review,” that row will be skipped automatically.

